            "answer_feedback": "You're staring down the barrel of a gun. The crowd roars. For an agonizing second, you're frozen in time. What a tragedy, you haven't been enlightened yet. The fire consumes you. The wheel spins, and the cycle continues. Will your next life be as interesting as this one? Time to find out."
        }
    },
    {
        "model": "campaign_trail.answer_feedback",
        "pk": 13076,
        "fields": {
            "answer": 12794,
            "candidate": 92,
            "answer_feedback": "Many in the party still recognize you as Lyndon's waterboy. It's good to change perceptions, but this just doesn't hit the spot. Helms and Thurmond like your tone, and so does everyone south of the Mason-Dixon, but you're hurting yourself with the North."
        }
