        "pk": 13079,
        "fields": {
            "answer": 13077,
            "candidate": 92,
            "answer_feedback": "Dole slicks his hand up, but it's unnecessary. The sheer dirt and grease from party men slathers up his hand anyway. Any concerns about you in their minds seem to slip away for a moment once they slather up Bob's hand. They don't care about your activities before 73. They see you for what you really are. One of them."
