ingly, they sought moderation over basic economic populism, the same strategy that sank my father's presidency in the 1992 election. A <span style=\\\"text-decoration: underline;\\\">new report</span> from the Center for Working Class Politics indicates that the dropping of basic economic policies such as the raising of the Minimum wage to 12 dollars from the 2016 campaign was disastrous for the Democratic party's already dying working class base, and directly brought about Brownback's landslide in 2020.</p>\\n\\n        <p>Brownback’s tenure was a dystopian experiment in unfettered supply-side economics. From the forced dissolution of the Department of Education to the privatization of the national parks, his administration sought to fulfill the dream that Richard Nixon’s political dynasty—a machine that brought us the Southern Strategy, the normalization of executive impunity, and the initial, creeping decay of industrial democracy—stoked the fires of the collapse of what little progress was made in the economic and social development of our wildly undemocratic democracy. Or, 'constitutional republic', as Brownback would say.</p>\\n\\n        <p>With the victory of a self-pronounced 'Democratic Socialist' the American people have finally found their breath of fresh air. Yet, the liberal coalition that has throughly burrowed it's tendrils within the Democratic party's structure has only been shaken. If you listen to some liberals—I won't be naming names—AOC's narrow primary victory and subsequent landslide victory was a fluke. They'd whine and say Dean Philips would've won by more, would've rallied the suburbanities and moderate Republicans to exceed AOC's 366 electoral vote margin. Yet, <span style=\\\"text-decoration: underline;\\\">most polls</span> point to AOC simply being a better candidate than Philips. The reality of the situation is that AOC did not win in spite of her socialist leanings, she won because of them. Many Philips supporters did not vote for her, in fact, many voted <I>against</I> her in the general election.</p>\\n\\n        <p>The same voters who voted to nominate a man who cheated on his dying wife with cancer, the same voters who voted for Warner over a socialist who had been there to march for civil rights in the 60s, are the same voters who held their noses and did not vote for their own nominee. The establishment is not\\n just held up by bribing whatever schmuck occupies the White House, it is held up by the electorate themselves. The concept of Middle America, a mass of god-fearing, patriotic citizens with total loyalty to the government has not been a constant throughout American history, as many reactionaries would like you to believe. Middle America manifested after the American public vindicated the likes of Richard Nixon after his acquittal in 1978 in spite of the overwhelming evidence of his crookedness.</p>\\n\\n        <p>AOC has a mandate not seen since the days of FDR. The ousting of Kaine and Jeffries from their leadership positions has allowed Congress to be dominated by progressive leaders ready to usher in her agenda. The years of regression we have faced seem to be reversing. Yet, unless broad structural reform within the whole of American society is pursued, we may find ourselves falling once more into another cycle. Unless we turn the wheel to break the chains of capital itself, when will we find ourselves back in 1976? When will another Nixon, another Connally, be in control of this land? Social Democratic policies may allieviate temporary pains we face today, but we Socialists should not take this for granted. We cannot see the enactment of the Green New Deal, the passing of the PRO Act, and the passing of Medicare for all as the end goal. We cannot grow complacent. We must see Cortez as a entryist gateway to greater progress. Now, more than ever.</p>\\n    </div>\\n\\n    <!-- Links Section -->\\n    <div style=\\\"margin-top: 50px; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; padding-top: 20px;\\\">\\n        <h3 style=\\\"font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 15px;\\\">Related Articles</h3>\\n        <ul style=\\\"list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0; line-height: 1.8;\\\">\\n            <li><a href=\\\"#\\\" style=\\\"color: #ed1c24; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;\\\">[+] Sexual Predator Donald Trump Barely Leads Polls Against DSA Backed Zohran Mamdani in Mayor Race</a></li>\\n            <li><a href=\\\"#\\\" style=\\\"color: #ed1c24; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;\\\">[+] Jesse Ventura announces primary challenge against Governor Klobuchar</a></li>\\n            <li><a href=\\\"#\\\" style=\\\"color: #ed1c24; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;\\\">[+] Chelsea Clinton Converts Her Father To Socialism Using Benjamin Netanyahu</a></li>\\n            <li><a href=\\\"#\\\" style=\\\"color: #ed1c24; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;\\\">[+] Senate Majority Leader Hunter Biden's Promise of Retribution Against Wannabe Dictator Bukele</a></li>\\n        </ul>\\n    </div>\\n</div>\",\n    \"image\": \"\",\n    \"slideGroup\": \"secondary\",\n    \"variableConditions\": [],\n    \"variableConditionOperator\": \"AND\",\n    \"answerConditionType\": \"ignore\",\n    \"answerConditionAnswer\": \"\",\n    \"answerConditionAnswers\": \"\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"variable\": 0,\n    \"operator\": \"<\",\n    \"amount\": 172,\n    \"outcomeCondition\": \"ignore\",\n    \"title\": \"\",\n    \"subtitle\": \"\",\n    \"content\": \"<style>\\n    /* Scope within TCT to avoid ruining base UI */\\n    .wiki-table-container {\\n        font-family: sans-serif;\\n        font-size: 13px;\\n    }\\n    .wp-pres-table {\\n        border-collapse: collapse;\\n        width: 100%;\\n        background-color: white;\\n        border: 1px solid #a2a9b1;\\n    }\\n    .wp-pres-table td {\\n        border: 1px solid #a2a9b1;\\n        padding: 5px;\\n        text-align: center;\\n        vertical-align: middle;\\n    }\\n    .wp-pres-t